{
  "children": [
    {
      "name": "ProjectHandler",
      "purpose": "Handles create, update, and delete project commands. Validates input, checks member existence for owner, updates project data, and cascades deletion to tasks when deleting a project.",
      "inputs": [
        {"name": "command", "type": "str", "description": "One of 'create_project', 'update_project', 'delete_project'", "source": "parent"},
        {"name": "data", "type": "dict", "description": "Project data containing fields like name, description, owner_id, project_id, etc.", "source": "parent"}
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {"name": "result", "type": "dict", "description": "Response with success, message, and data fields", "consumer": "parent"}
      ],
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": ["Project CRUD operations", "Owner existence validation", "Cascade delete tasks on project deletion", "Automatic project_id generation for create"],
        "out_of_scope": ["Task status updates", "Member availability changes", "Listing queries"]
      },
      "behavior": "For 'create_project': Checks owner exists via members.get; if not, returns error. Creates project via projects.create with default status 'planning' and auto-generated id and creation time. For 'update_project': Checks project exists; if not, error. If owner_id provided, checks owner exists. Updates project with provided fields. For 'delete_project': Checks project exists; lists all tasks of project via tasks.list; for each task, if assigned, updates member availability to 'available'; then deletes tasks; finally deletes project. Returns success with appropriate message.",
      "signature": "def ProjectHandler(command: str, data: dict) -> dict",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": "",
      "global_vars": [
        {"variable": "members", "op": "read", "description": "Read member data for owner existence check"},
        {"variable": "projects", "op": "read_write", "description": "Create, update, delete projects"},
        {"variable": "tasks", "op": "read_write", "description": "Read and delete tasks on project deletion"}
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "TaskHandler",
      "purpose": "Handles create, assign, update status, complete, and delete task commands. Manages task lifecycle and member assignment.",
      "inputs": [
        {"name": "command", "type": "str", "description": "One of 'create_task', 'assign_task', 'update_task_status', 'complete_task', 'delete_task'", "source": "parent"},
        {"name": "data", "type": "dict", "description": "Task data containing task_id, project_id, assignee_id, etc.", "source": "parent"}
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {"name": "result", "type": "dict", "description": "Response with success, message, and data fields", "consumer": "parent"}
      ],
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": ["Task CRUD", "Task status transitions (todo->in_progress->review->done, blocked anytime)", "Assignment logic (check task unassigned, member available, optional skill match)", "Completion with actual hours recording", "Release member on complete or delete", "Validation of project status for create task (planning or active)"],
        "out_of_scope": ["Project CRUD", "Member CRUD", "Listing queries"]
      },
      "behavior": "For 'create_task': Validates project exists and status in ['planning','active']; creates task with default status 'todo' and no assignee. For 'assign_task': Checks task exists and is unassigned; checks member exists and available; optionally checks skills; updates task assignee_id; sets member availability to 'busy'. For 'update_task_status': Checks task exists; validates status transition (todo->in_progress->review->done; blocked allowed anytime); if status becomes done, records actual hours from data (if provided, else 0); updates task. For 'complete_task': Checks task status is 'review'; sets status to 'done'; records actual hours from data; updates task; releases member by setting availability to 'available'. For 'delete_task': Checks task exists; if assigned, releases member; deletes task. Returns success.",
      "signature": "def TaskHandler(command: str, data: dict) -> dict",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": "",
      "global_vars": [
        {"variable": "projects", "op": "read", "description": "Read project status for create task validation"},
        {"variable": "members", "op": "read_write", "description": "Read member for assignment and update availability on assign/complete/delete"},
        {"variable": "tasks", "op": "read_write", "description": "Create, read, update, delete tasks"}
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "MemberHandler",
      "purpose": "Handles adding new members and updating member availability. Ensures data consistency.",
      "inputs": [
        {"name": "command", "type": "str", "description": "One of 'add_member', 'update_member_availability'", "source": "parent"},
        {"name": "data", "type": "dict", "description": "Member data containing member_id, name, role, skills, availability, etc.", "source": "parent"}
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {"name": "result", "type": "dict", "description": "Response with success, message, and data fields", "consumer": "parent"}
      ],
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": ["Member creation with unique ID", "Availability update with ongoing task check"],
        "out_of_scope": ["Task management", "Project operations"]
      },
      "behavior": "For 'add_member': Checks that member_id is unique (via members.exists); if exists, error. Creates member with provided fields (name, role, skills, availability default 'available'). For 'update_member_availability': Checks member exists; if setting to 'offline', checks that member has no ongoing tasks (tasks with assignee=member and status not in ['done','blocked']); if has ongoing, error; else updates availability. Returns success.",
      "signature": "def MemberHandler(command: str, data: dict) -> dict",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": "",
      "global_vars": [
        {"variable": "members", "op": "read_write", "description": "Create and update members"},
        {"variable": "tasks", "op": "read", "description": "Read tasks to check ongoing tasks for availability update"}
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "QueryHandler",
      "purpose": "Handles listing and querying operations: list project tasks, get member tasks, get project progress. Read-only operations.",
      "inputs": [
        {"name": "command", "type": "str", "description": "One of 'list_project_tasks', 'get_member_tasks', 'get_project_progress'", "source": "parent"},
        {"name": "data", "type": "dict", "description": "Query data containing filters like project_id, member_id, status_filter, etc.", "source": "parent"}
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {"name": "result", "type": "dict", "description": "Response with success, message, and data (list or progress info)", "consumer": "parent"}
      ],
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": ["Listing tasks by project with filters", "Getting tasks of a member with total hours", "Computing project progress metrics"],
        "out_of_scope": ["Modifications", "Member creation"]
      },
      "behavior": "For 'list_project_tasks': Optionally validates project exists; calls tasks.list with project_id and optional filters (status, priority, assignee); returns list of task details. For 'get_member_tasks': Optionally validates member exists; calls tasks.list with assignee=member_id; computes total hours (sum of actual_hours for tasks where actual_hours is not None); returns list and total. For 'get_project_progress': Validates project exists; gets all tasks of project; counts total tasks, completed tasks (status='done'), status counts, sum of estimated hours (from all tasks) and actual hours (from tasks with actual_hours), and estimated completion time (simple: remaining hours / average rate or just return data). Returns progress data.",
      "signature": "def QueryHandler(command: str, data: dict) -> dict",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": "",
      "global_vars": [
        {"variable": "projects", "op": "read", "description": "Read project info for validation and progress"},
        {"variable": "tasks", "op": "read", "description": "Read tasks for listing and progress computation"},
        {"variable": "members", "op": "read", "description": "Optionally read member for get_member_tasks to check existence"}
      ]
    }
  ],
  "decomposition_rationale": "The parent ProjectTaskManager routes incoming commands to one of four specialized children based on the command field. Each child handles a cohesive set of operations: ProjectHandler for project CRUD, TaskHandler for task lifecycle and assignment, MemberHandler for member creation and availability, and QueryHandler for read-only queries. This separation ensures each child has a clear responsibility, minimal overlap, and access only to the necessary global data stores through declared capabilities. The parent orchestrates by calling the appropriate child and returning its result."
}
